   <body>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC8171f3802519100584b5d8c3784850d2"></a>Refitting the timing belts
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12816"> </a>Rotate the pulleys on the timing layshaft until the timing mark on the outer pulley is aligned with the mark on the clutch
            cover.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12818"> </a>In this condition, the horizontal cylinder piston will be at top dead centre.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_013401844.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12823"> </a>Install in the generator cover seat the tool (A) no. <span class="bold">88713.2011</span> to prevent crankshaft rotation and lock it with the corresponding pin, by tightening the M8 screw of the tool to 20 Nm.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_013501845.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12831"> </a>To achieve correct timing, the screws (1) securing the pulleys to the hubs must be loose and positioned in the centre of their
            slots. 
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12834"> </a>First time the vertical cylinder head.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12836"> </a>Use tool (B) no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> to insert pins (C) in the camshaft seats (D).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_013601846.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_013701847.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12846"> </a>Position tool (B) no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> with writing “UP” and arrow facing the cylinder head cover.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12851"> </a>First position pins (C) of tool (B) no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> in the intake side pulley by using the key of tool (B) no. 88765.1623.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_013801848.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_013901849.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12862"> </a>Manually position pins (C) of tool (B) no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> in the exhaust side pulley.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_014001850.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12870"> </a>Manually screw the knobs of tool (B) no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> fully home.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_014101851.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12878"> </a>Use a torque screwdriver (E) to tighten the knob nuts of tool (B) no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> to 2 Nm ± 10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_014201852.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12886"> </a>Fit the vertical piston-cylinder assy timing belt around the camshaft pulleys and pass it behind the idler pulley.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12889"> </a>If the used belts are to be refitted, position them in their original direction of rotation and on their original cylinder.
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_014301853.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12894"> </a>Fit tensioner pulley (2) and washer (3) on the cylinder head pin.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12896"> </a>Apply specified grease to the tensioner pulley pin threads and the nut (8) mating face.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12898"> </a>Start the nut (4) on the crankshaft.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_014401854.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12904"> </a>Check the tensioning value and if necessary adjust vertical head belt (5) and horizontal head belt (6).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12907"> </a>Check the tensioning values on the belt branch (5) and on branch (L) of belt (6).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_014501855.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12912"> </a>Once the desired tension is reached make sure the fixing nut (4) of the mobile tensioner (2) is tightened to 25 Nm (Min. 22
            Nm - Max. 28 Nm) and vertical head screws (1) to 10 Nm (Min. 9 Nm - Max. 11 Nm).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_014601856.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12917"> </a>Remove tool (B) that blocks the camshafts no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> of the vertical cylinder head.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12922"> </a>First time the horizontal cylinder head.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12924"> </a>Use tool (B) no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> to insert pins (C) in the camshaft seats (D).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_013601846.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_014701857.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12934"> </a>Position tool (B) no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> with writing “UP” and arrow facing the cylinder head cover.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12939"> </a>Manually position the pins of tool (B) no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> in the seats (G) of the exhaust side pulley.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12944"> </a>Manually screw the knobs of tool (B) no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> fully home.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12949"> </a>Use a torque screwdriver (E) to tighten the knob nuts of tool (B) no. <span class="bold">88765.1623</span> to 2 Nm ± 10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_014801858.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12958"> </a>Fit the horizontal piston-cylinder assy timing belt around the camshaft pulleys and pass it behind the idler tensioner.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12961"> </a>If the used belts are to be refitted, position them in their original direction of rotation and on their original cylinder.
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_014901859.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12966"> </a>Fit tensioner pulley (2) and washer (3) on the cylinder head pin.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12968"> </a>Apply specified grease to the tensioner pulley threads and the nut (4) mating face.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12970"> </a>Start the nut (4) on the crankshaft.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_015001860.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12975"> </a>Check the tensioning value and if necessary adjust the horizontal head belt tension.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12977"> </a>Once the desired tension is reached make sure the fixing nut (4) of the mobile tensioner (2) is tightened to 25 Nm (Min. 22
            Nm - Max. 28 Nm) and horizontal head screws (1) to 10 Nm (Min. 9 Nm - Max. 11 Nm). 
         </div>
      </div>
